[[— DECISION 1 — The Bag]]

:: — DECISION 1 — The Bag {"position":"700,1525","size":"100,100"}
Three days after Combo.

Jesse's apartment. The bag of blue is on the coffee table where he left it. Skinny Pete's been calling — the Ortega brothers want a sample meet tonight and Jesse is the one who has to show up and look like he has his shit together.

He's been clean for three days. His hands are shaking.

The bag just sits there. It doesn't do anything. It doesn't have to.

[[Use it — KP -2]]
[[Leave it — KP +2]]


:: Use it — KP -2 {"position":"575,1650","size":"100,100"}
(set: $karma to $karma - 2)
You open the bag.

The meet goes smooth. The Ortegas are impressed. Jesse keeps his voice even the whole time.
When he gets home Jane is already asleep. He stands in the doorway and watches her breathe for a while.

She doesn't know. And he isn't going to tell her.

[[— DECISION 2 — The Territory Call]]


:: Leave it — KP +2 {"position":"825,1650","size":"100,100"}
(set: $karma to $karma + 2)
You put the bag in the kitchen drawer. Walk away. Don't look back.

The meet is harder. Jesse's hands sweat through the handshake. But he holds it together.
When he gets home Jane is awake on the couch, reading. She looks up and smiles when she sees him.

She can tell something's different. She doesn't ask what.

[[— DECISION 2 — The Territory Call]]


:: — DECISION 2 — The Territory Call {"position":"700,1775","size":"100,100"}
A parking lot, late. Jesse, Skinny Pete, and Badger count cash on the hood of Pete's car.

<div style="text-align:center; margin:20px 0;">
  <iframe src="Videos/4.mp4" width="600" height="400" style="max-width:90%; border:0; border-radius:8px;" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div>

Pete tells Jesse that Mr. White wants to push into Salamanca territory. They all look at Jesse — he's the one with the Walt connection. If this goes sideways it goes sideways on all of them.

[[Back Walt's Plan — KP -2]]
[[Push Back — KP +2]]


:: Back Walt's Plan — KP -2 {"position":"575,1900","size":"100,100"}
(set: $karma to $karma - 2)
"Walt knows what he's doing. We trust the plan."

Pete looks uncomfortable. Badger stares at the ground.

Something shifts in how they look at Jesse that night. He notices it and files it.
On the drive home he tells himself Walt's been right about everything so far.

He almost believes it.

[[— DECISION 3 — The Dinner]]


:: Push Back — KP +2 {"position":"825,1900","size":"100,100"}
(set: $karma to $karma + 2)
"I'll talk to Walt. We keep it small or I'm out."

Pete nods, relieved. Badger fist bumps him.
Jesse calls Walt that night. Walt listens to everything he says and then dismisses every single point, calmly, like a man explaining long division to a child.

Jesse stays on the line another two minutes saying "yeah" until he can hang up without it being weird.

Something has started to shift.

[[— DECISION 3 — The Dinner]]


:: — DECISION 3 — The Dinner {"position":"700,2025","size":"100,100"}
Two weeks later. Jane's apartment, early Sunday.

She asks Jesse to come to dinner with her dad. Donald Margolis — air traffic controller, recovering alcoholic himself, man who asks careful questions. Jesse can feel the table already. The pauses. The way Donald would look at him.

Jane isn't pressuring him. She's just asking. She looks at him the way she always does, like she already knows the answer and she's just waiting for him to catch up.

[["I'll be there." — KP +3]]
[["I can't. I got stuff with Walt." — KP -3]]


:: "I'll be there." — KP +3 {"position":"825,2150","size":"100,100"}
(set: $karma to $karma + 3)
Sunday dinner. Pot roast. Donald asks Jesse how he spends his time.

Jesse says distribution. Donald nods like that could mean anything.
It's awkward. Jesse says the wrong things twice and the right thing once, by accident. Donald doesn't fully trust him. But he doesn't write him off either.

On the drive home Jane says: "He liked you."

Jesse doesn't say anything. But he keeps the window up so she can't see him smiling.

[[— Act 1 End]]


:: "I can't. I got stuff with Walt." — KP -3 {"position":"575,2150","size":"100,100"}
(set: $karma to $karma - 3)
Jane stops talking about her dad after that.

Stops talking about a lot of things.
A week later Jesse finds an old kit under the bathroom sink, tucked behind the cleaning supplies. He stares at it for a long time. He puts it back exactly where he found it. He doesn't say anything.

She doesn't say anything either.

[[— Act 1 End]]


:: — Act 1 End {"position":"700,2275","size":"100,100"}
