He doesn't sleep. He stops being Jesse Pinkman and becomes something smaller that has no name.
Walt dies in the lab.

Shot. By the machine gun he built. For the same people he chose over Jesse, over and over, until Jesse was the only one left to save and Walt had nothing left to spend.
Saul ends up in Omaha.

Managing a Cinnabon.

He wears a different name. He watches the door. He doesn't call anyone he used to know.

Some mornings, when the mall is quiet, he thinks about the motel room. The kid with his hands between his knees.

The thing he didn't say.

---

*There are no winners in Albuquerque.*

*Some people don't even make it out.*

