:: Get Jesse Out - Good Ending {"position":"1100,3650","size":"100,100"}
"I know a guy. Not the rehab kind. The disappearing kind. New name, new state. You drive north and you don't come back."

Jesse stares at the carpet.

"Alaska," he says finally.

"Sure. Alaska. Why not Alaska."

Two weeks later, Saul drives Jesse to a pull-off past the city limits. A plain white van is idling. Jesse gets out with a backpack and nothing else.

He doesn't hug Saul. Doesn't say thank you.

He nods once.

Saul nods back.

The van drives north.

When Saul gets back to the office, Heisenberg is going to call and ask where his partner went. Saul is going to lie to his face.

For the first time in a long time, he's going to sleep fine that night.

Three months later, Walter White drives to the police station on a Tuesday morning, asks for a cup of coffee, and waits. The cancer has come back, stage four. He'd known for six weeks. He didn't want to die in the lab. He didn't want to die as Heisenberg.

The confession takes four hours. Every name. Every corner. Every cook site.

Skyler keeps the house. Flynn doesn't speak to his father for two years, and then he does.

Saul closes his practice on a Friday. Drives west. Opens something smaller and quieter. Sleeps fine.

---

*Jesse Pinkman drove north and kept driving.*

*He changed his name. He learned to work with his hands.*

*He built things.*

*He never cooked again.*

---

**[END — GOOD PATH]**


