:: — ACT 3 — Saul — Jane Alive {"position":"300,2700","size":"100,100"}
Dawn at the strip mall.

<div style="text-align:center; margin:20px 0;">
  <iframe src="Videos/9.mp4" width="600" height="400" style="max-width:90%; border:0; border-radius:8px;" allow="autoplay; fullscreen" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</div>

Saul Goodman — real name James McGill, age undisclosed, height whatever the shoes say — unlocks Saul Goodman and Associates.

There are no associates.

He brews constitutional coffee. The difference this morning — the thing sitting differently in his chest — is that the girl is alive.

He knows what Walt almost did. He knows because Walt called at 3 AM, voice too steady. The kind of steady that only happens after someone has just decided something and hasn't processed it yet.

*She's fine. Jesse's fine.*

The way Walt said *fine* told Saul everything.

The burner rings. It's the Kid.

[[Jesse Calls - Jane Alive]]


:: Jesse Calls - Jane Alive {"position":"300,2875","size":"100,100"}
"Yo, it's me."

"I know it's you. What's happening?"

"Jane's alive."

A pause. Like Jesse is still surprised by it.

"She's okay. She was — it was bad, but she's okay. And Saul, I think Mr. White was there. Jane told me. She saw him. Standing there. Just standing there."

"And then she said he reached down and rolled her over."

Saul stares at the Statue of Liberty through the window.

*He reached down and rolled her over.*

After all the inches Walt has been sliding in one direction, he stopped at the last one.

"Come to the office. Bring Jane. Don't call Walt yet."

[[The Office Meeting - Jane Alive]]


:: The Office Meeting - Jane Alive {"position":"300,3050","size":"100,100"}
Jesse and Jane come in looking like they haven't slept.

Jane has bruises under her eyes. She sits straight anyway.

Saul lays it out: Walt's operation is growing, Gus Fring is circling, the DEA is getting closer. This is the part of the roller coaster where you can still see the platform.

"You have a window. Both of you. You leave now, you can have a life that isn't this."

Jesse asks: *What about Mr. White?*

*What do you tell him?*

[[Tell Jesse Walt Saved Jane - Jane Alive]]
[[Don't Tell Jesse - Jane Alive]]


:: Don't Tell Jesse - Jane Alive {"position":"150,3225","size":"100,100"}
"Walt's not your problem anymore. He made his choices. You make yours."

Jesse doesn't look satisfied. But he nods.

Jane squeezes his hand.

"Okay. So how do we do this?"

Saul starts making calls.

[[Planning the Exit - Jane Alive]]


:: Tell Jesse Walt Saved Jane - Jane Alive {"position":"450,3225","size":"100,100"}
"He was there. In your apartment. He saw what was happening and he — he rolled her over."

Jesse stares.

"He saved her."

The silence in the room is thick.

Jesse looks at the table. Something moves across his face — complicated, ugly, honest.

"Why?"

"I don't know. Maybe he's not as far gone as either of us thought."

Jane is very still. "What happens to him?"

"That," Saul says carefully, "is going to be up to him."

[[Planning the Exit - Jane Alive]]


:: Planning the Exit - Jane Alive {"position":"300,3400","size":"100,100"}
The problem is Walt.

Walt knows everything — every cook site, every contact, every number. If he decides Jesse leaving is a threat, it becomes one.

"You're going to need to talk to him," Saul says. "Tell him you're out. You don't ask. You tell him."

Jesse looks at the door like it's the last door he ever wants to walk through.

*How does Jesse approach Walt?*

[[Jesse Confronts Walt Directly - Jane Alive]]
[[Jesse Sends Walt a Message Through Saul - Jane Alive]]


:: Jesse Sends Walt a Message Through Saul - Jane Alive {"position":"150,3575","size":"100,100"}
Saul calls Walt.

Simple. Jesse's done. He's going somewhere Walt can't follow. No negotiation.

Walt is quiet for a long time.

"Is he safe?"

"He will be."

Another pause.

"...okay."

Not forgiveness. Not resolution. Just Walt saying okay and hanging up.

But it's enough.

[[Walt's Choice - Jane Alive]]


:: Jesse Confronts Walt Directly - Jane Alive {"position":"450,3575","size":"100,100"}
Jesse drives to Walt's house early. Walt answers the door in his robe.

He looks older than Jesse remembers. Or maybe Jesse is just looking properly for the first time.

"I'm out. I'm not asking. I'm telling you."

Walt looks at him for a long time.

"You sure?"

"Yeah."

Walt nods slowly. Looks past Jesse at the street. At the ordinary world he's been steadily destroying from the inside.

"Take care of yourself, Jesse."

He goes back inside. The door closes.

Jesse stands on the porch for a moment. Then he walks to his car and drives away and doesn't look back.

[[Walt's Choice - Jane Alive]]


:: Walt's Choice - Jane Alive {"position":"300,3750","size":"100,100"}
Walt sits at the kitchen table for three hours.

Skyler at work. Flynn at school. The house the quietest place on earth.

He thinks about Jesse. About the girl. About the moment in that apartment when his hand stopped in the air and then kept moving anyway, and what that means about who he still is underneath everything he's become.

He thinks about Gus Fring waiting on the other end of a call he hasn't made yet.

He thinks about what happens if he makes it.

*What does Walt do?*

[[Walt Walks Away - Good Ending]]
[[Walt Makes the Call - Bad Ending]]


:: Walt Walks Away - Good Ending {"position":"150,3925","size":"100,100"}
Walt doesn't make the call.

He sits at the table until Skyler comes home. She walks in and stops when she sees him sitting there in the middle of the afternoon.

"Walt?"

"I want to stop. I need to tell you everything. And then I want to stop."

Four hours. Skyler doesn't say much. Asks a few questions. Cries once, quietly, with her back to him. She doesn't forgive him that day, or the next week, or the month after.

But she doesn't leave.

Walt cooperates with the DEA through a separate lawyer. He gives them everything. Cook sites, contacts, money trails. In exchange: a reduced sentence, proximity to family, access to a hospital.

The cancer responds to treatment. Barely. But it does.

---

*Walter White served four years.*

*He came home to a smaller house and a family still learning how to be one.*

*He never cooked again.*

---

Jesse and Jane crossed the state line on a Thursday afternoon, windows down, a bad radio signal picking up a country station out of Colorado.

Jane changed her name. Jesse didn't — he figured he'd earned the right to keep it.

He learned to build furniture. He was good at it. The kind of good that comes from starting over five times before you get it right.

---

*Saul Goodman closed his practice on a Friday.*

*He drove west. Opened something smaller. Quieter.*

*Took cases that didn't require a burner phone.*

*He slept fine.*

---

---

*There are no winners in Albuquerque.*

*But sometimes people choose to stop losing.*

---

**[END — GOOD PATH, ALL THREE]**


:: Walt Makes the Call - Bad Ending {"position":"450,3925","size":"100,100"}
Walt picks up the phone.

He dials.

Gus Fring picks up on the second ring, like he's been waiting.

*That's the thing about Walt. He always knows when he's making the wrong choice. He makes it anyway.*

The operation scales up. The laundry. The superlab. Industrial quantities across three states.

Jesse and Jane are safe — they got out, Saul made sure of that.

But Walt is still in it, deeper than ever, and the machine he built doesn't have a reverse gear.

Gus dies. The cartel burns. Hank gets close. Then Hank gets too close.

Walt makes choices that can't be unmade. He poisons a child to keep Jesse in line. He watches Hank die. He watches everything collapse anyway.

He dies in the superlab on a cold night in November. Shot by a machine gun he built, triggered by a key fob. He gets to the floor and touches the equipment on the way down. Cold steel. Clean surfaces.

He built something perfect, and it destroyed everything that mattered.

Saul ends up in Omaha. Managing a Cinnabon. He wears a different name and watches the door.

He thinks about Jesse and Jane sometimes. Hopes they made it somewhere good.

He never finds out.

---

*Jesse and Jane drove north and didn't look back.*

*Walt chose the empire.*

*The empire chose him back.*

---

